==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Womanly
<hw>Wom"an*ly</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Becoming a woman; feminine;
<as>as, <ex>womanly</ex> behavior</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Arbuthnot.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A blushing, <qex>womanly</qex> discovering grace.</q>
<rj><qau>Donne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Womanly</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Womanly
<hw>Wom"an*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In the manner of a woman; with
the grace, tenderness, or affection of a woman.</def>
<rj><au>Gascoigne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Woman's Christian Temperance Union</ent>⟦br⟧
